	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">Part 2:  To Thurgadin<br />
<br />
The weathered dwarf sat on a nearby rock and began to ruffle with his pack.  “This calls for a change of plans.”  He removed a water skin and three small “toy” hammers from his backpack and replaced them with his mace.  He carefully hung each small mace from his belt, then took a giant swig from his water skin, dripping some down his beard.  “Nothing like dwarven water to get da juices flowin!” he smiled as he wiped the ale from his beard.  Quickly returning his backpack to its place the dwarf stood and stared at the Great Divide…the treacherous path that would lead him and his friends to Thurgadin.  He wondered, for the first time, whether they would all make it alive.<br />
<br />
“Hey fatty!  Do you really think this is a good time to drink ale?”  an unkown voice called from behind Gnarm.<br />
<br />
“Who?  What?”  Gnarm exclaimed as he swung around searching for the mysterious voice.<br />
<br />
“Hehe you aren’t going to see me you crazy dwarf.” The hint of laughter could be heard from the unkown speaker.<br />
<br />
“Well I’ll be an elf’s uncle!  Fistel!”  Gnarm howled as he realized who the anonymous speaker was.  “Show yourself friend!”<br />
<br />
Sitting on the rock that the dwarf had just got up from appeared a well kept Gnome in a white robe.  His face not showing the age that his white hair suggested.  The smallest patch of hair protruded from the gnomes chin, something he had very fervently explained to Gnarm many times was a “goatee.”<br />
<br />
“Hello cousin!  Heard you were on an adventure and you know me I’m always up for an adventure.”<br />
<br />
“Glad ye could make it brother.  Everyone meet Fistel, Master Illusionist, and a fellow Brellian!  Fistel meet me friends…the big dumb lookin human over der is Graydon, he a paladin, the skimpy, quiet half-elf right der is Aranthus, he says he a wizard but he more like one o dem joustin dummies, and da energetic lass over der is Loryann, she’s our tracker and quite an ANNOYIN’ one at dat.”<br />
<br />
“Well met all.”  Fistel bowed to the friends in turn as they were introduced.<br />
<br />
“Well what’s everybody standin around fer?  Ye act like yer waiting fer me ta start <a href="http://www.eqcleric.com/forums/showthread.php?s=&postid=13920#post13920" target="_blank">jumping over Fistel</a> or some such nonsense.  Lets move.”  Gnarm didn’t wait for a response and plodded through the knee deep snow towards the great divide.<br />
<br />
By the time they had entered the Great Divide the sun was long gone and the harsh winds of the north showed why few dared travel in the northern lands of Norath.  <br />
<br />
“A good place for an ambush.”  Graydon pointed out. “We should be quite wary, Rockem is not as dumb as some of his kin.”<br />
<br />
“Aye, dat why we movin through da night, no rest till Thurgadin.”<br />
<br />
“Aww…but what about dinner, and after dinner snack, and bedtime snack?”  The Halfling stuck her lower lip out in a quite sincere gesture of displeasure.<br />
<br />
“Ha ha got it all right here lass!”  Gnarm stated as he patted his water skin full of ‘Dwarven water.’<br />
<br />
“Humph.  Laugh now but when I die of hunger you’ll be sorry.”<br />
<br />
“Bah, enough dramatics and keep yer eye on the path.  Scout ahead for giants…it’ll take yer mind off missin three of yer eighteen meals t’day.”<br />
<br />
“I only have 10 meals a day like any other Halfling, thank you very MUCH!”  Loryann stuck her tongue out at the dwarf as she bounded ahead in search of signs of danger.<br />
<br />
“Ye can’t eat if yer ded lass!”  Gnarm yelled after her.  “Hehe I gots da last word on da one.”  He turned and stated to Fistel.<br />
<br />
“I wouldn’t be so sure of that fatty.”<br />
<br />
“What do you mean?”  Gnarm turned away from the Gnome just in time to see the pebble that was about to smack him in the forehead.  Startled Gnarm attempted to move, but was too late and the pebble stuck the unbalanced dwarf right between his eyes sending him sprawling into the snow.  Fistel’s laughed so hard at this that he had to get down on his knees to settle himself.<br />
<br />
“Go ahead and laugh…why don’t you just yell out ‘Hey Giants come kill us we are right here!’ Dern Gnome.”  Gnarm brushed off the snow from his beard and scowled at the Gnome.<br />
<br />
“Come on cousin all in good fun.”  Fistel was trying hard to fight back the urge to laugh more, so much that tears were welling up in his eyes.<br />
<br />
“Humph.  Let’s get movin.  No tellin what kind of beasties be layin in wait fer us.”  With that the dwarf started off again.  Trudging through the snow and harsh wind of the daunting Great Divide.<br />
<br />
Soon after the snow began to fall and Loryann returned to the group.  “I found some tracks, three maybe 4 giants have been through here in the past half hour or so.”<br />
<br />
“Dat sounds like our welcoming party.”  Gnarm rubbed his hands together, smiling widely. “Let’s go show dem how much we appreciate em.”<br />
<br />
“Fistel since ye’s got flyin an hidin majiks go over dat ridge der…der be a fort just beyond.  I needs ya ta spy on da one dey call Rockem Dwarfsmasher, he live in dat fort.  Find out what he up ta.”<br />
<br />
Fistel seemed not to hear him and just stared out over the horizon.<br />
<br />
“Fistel!  Wake up!”<br />
<br />
“Oh, sorry…smoke err never mind.  What was it you wanted?”<br />
<br />
Gnarm repeated his instructions impatiently to the gnome.<br />
<br />
“Um shouldn’t someone else do that?  Giants seem to like to chew on me.”  <br />
<br />
“Pfft go lad ain’t nobody else as qualified.”<br />
<br />
Fistel sighed and chanted the words to his spell to make him float then a few more words and the gnome was gone from site.<br />
<br />
______________________________________<br />
<br />
“He lived!”  Rockem’s face was red with fury.  “You idiot…now he’ll know we know and will try to thwart us!”<br />
<br />
The other giants around Rockem scratched there heads in and looked around, confused.<br />
<br />
“He knows we want to kill him you idiots!”  Rockem swung his fist connecting squarely with the jaw of his closest kin, knocking him to the ground.<br />
<br />
“You!”  He pointed at his finest giant warrior, Gromdor, “Take your best men out and kill the dwarf!  I have plans for the complete destruction of Thurgadin to finalize before we attack in the morning.”<br />
<br />
“Yes high one.”  Gromdor gathered up the other giants and left their master’s room.<br />
<br />
Rockem contemplated over his plans.  They were good, better than any before them.  This time the Frost Giants of the Great Divide will be victorious against Thurgadin.  They had everything on there side…surprise, strength and this time there would be no meddling adventurers to help Thurgadin.  The giant sat back in his chair and let a smile cross his face.  Yes tomorrow would be a good day.  He was so happy with himself he failed to notice the slight breeze coming from the open window.<br />
<br />
“Not good” the invisible Fistel thought as he stared at the giants plans for tomorrow. “This is notgoodatall!”  He quickly zipped out the window to catch up with the group and spread the dire news.<br />
<br />
_________________________________<br />
<br />
The group traveled quickly up the path, eyes darting from side to side looking for signs of an ambush coming to a halt just a few hundred meters short of the area Gnarm said the ambush would most likely come.  <br />
<br />
“Der.”  Gnarm pointed at the cliff sides ahead “Dat be where da giants are.  It da thinnest part o da divide an the walls are very steep.  Dey would pelt us ta death with rocks an we wouldn’t be able to do a dern thin about it.”  He scratched his beard trying to come up with a plan, it wasn’t long before Graydon noticed a spark in the dwarfs eye.  “Ah here da plan lads and lass.  Loryann ye gonna sneak by dem, get a few hundred feet from dem an build a small fire.  Soon as da fire built ye gonna come back.  When she get back we moving forward.  Da giants will see da fire and go investigate…and then we will have da advantage.”<br />
<br />
With nothing else being said the Halfling slipped into the shadows and raced off towards her goal.  Gnarm took this opportunity to prepare himself.  He returned his water skin to his bag and strapped his shield to his back, freeing up his other had.  Then sat down and contemplated the prayers he would need for the battle ahead.<br />
<br />
It wasn’t long before the Loyann came running back.  “Um small change of plans…they saw me!”  Loryann screamed as she neared the group.<br />
<br />
Graydon quickly drew his matching long swords and readied himself.  Before he could see anyone or anything a boulder came from above and struck him in the shoulder, knocking him off balance a second soon behind it glancing of the side of his head, knocking him back into the snow.  <br />
<br />
Loyann deftly dodged two boulders intended for her and arrived with the rest of the group.  “They’re up on the ridge.  Both sides of us, four of them I think.”  She drew her bow and began to litter the ridge side with her arrows.<br />
<br />
Graydon quickly pulled himself out of the snow and again readied his swords.  “We can’t just stand here, we have to rush one side or the other.”  As he said this, another boulder struck him in the back knocking him to his knees.  <br />
<br />
“Aye yer right friend.  Follow me!”  Gnarm raced towards the right side of the Divide his fellow adventurers in tow.  “Dis be da easiest place ta climb.  GO!”  The giants behind them had begun to discend the ridge side headed in there direction.  The giants above them were out of sight now and that worried Gnarm, they were vulnerable right now, very vulnerable.<br />
<br />
Graydon was first to the summit, and barely saw the hammer swing that took him off his feet and sent him tumbling back down to the bottom of the Great Divide.  The determined paladin attempted to stand, quickly realizing that both his legs were severely broken as well as an arm and several ribs.<br />
<br />
Gnarm saw the paladin take the vicious blow and watched him tumble down the divide, unable to help.  Anger began to well up in the dwarf as he saw his friend of over twenty seasons struggle to stand and fail.  He began to chant his most powerful war song as fast as he possible could, praying to Brell for his greatest healing gift.  He saw the action around him as Loryann and Aranthus attempted to hold off the two giants at the top of the hill while Graydon lay helpless at the bottom of the hill, near death and two giants quickly approaching him.  Gnarm picked up the pace of his chant and prayed that it would finish in time.  As the final syllables of his pray were muttered Graydon was covered in a bright white light descending from the sky, blinding the two giants who were just about to crush the defenseless paladin.  <br />
<br />
Graydon felt the soothing light wash over him and embraced it.  He could feel his broken limbs and ribs mend and the cuts all over his body close.  The confusion brought by the excruciating pain was gone because there was no pain.  He stood and brought his weapons of choice to bear faced the startled giants on even terms again.  Well at least two on one was as close to even as he could give them.<br />
<br />
Gnarm cracked a smile as his good friend stood and flashed his fine blades.  ‘Glad I got to ya in time friend…dat was too close’ he said to himself.  He turned to assess the others situation.  One giant seemed to be stuck in place pulling at his legs but not getting any where, the smoke was rising from the other at place where his beard and hair had been, apparently the result of one of Aranthus’ spells.  Gnarm unconsciously grabbed his beard, “Good thing dat lad be on my side.”  Loyann was deftly slashing the hairless giant while dodging his attempts to crush her.  “Well dey ain’t doin bad at all” he said as whispered a pray to Brell sending healing energies to Loryann, ensuring her wounds would heal as she received them for a time.<br />
<br />
“Well den looks like I gonna be needin’ a weapon.” Gnarm raised his hand high and prayed for Brell to grant him his request.  As the prayer finished the clouds split and a dark purple lightning bolt struck Gnarm’s raised hand, hurting no one but leaving in it’s wake a magnificent weapon.  The maul was nearly as tall as Gnarm himself, the shaft beautifully crafted and adorned with shining rubies.  On the head of the giant maul A large holy symbol of the Lord Underfoot resided Glowing in a powerful blue light.  “Har har now dat is a hammer!”  Gnarm shouted with glee as he ran up the ridge.<br />
<br />
As he reached the top of the ridge Gnarm began a prayer and removed one of the small hammers hanging from his belt.  When he finished the prayer he flung the small hammer at the singed giant as it neared the giant the hammer stopped and grew an easy ten times bigger than it was before, then began to swing at the giant as if being wielded by an beserk invisible ally.  “Hehe PET!”  Gnarm smiled again.  “Told ye we were gonna have some fun!”<br />
<br />
The stocky dwarf charged at the unsuspecting stuck giant leaping shoulder first into it’s knee.  He could hear the giants joint pop as his shoulder connected, and the giant dropped to his knees.  Going with his momentum Gnarm rolled to his feet behind the giant.  “Well now dat I got ya ta a more manageable height lemme see how far I can smack ye!”  Holding on to the leather straps at the base of his Divine gift weapon Gnarm spun on his heals using the all of his force to swing the maul into the back of the giant.  As the maul connected a loud booming went off signaling the hidden power of the hammer had been unleashed.  The giant let out a gurgled moan and fell lifeless to the ground.  “Bah dey just don’t make Giants like dey used to.”<br />
<br />
Loryann and Aranthus had managed to fell their giant, and the three raced down the ridge towards Graydon.<br />
<br />
To this point Graydon had held his own…but barely.  It had been a draw to this point between he and the giants.  The taller of the two giants wielded a giant greatsword and did so with great skill…nearly matching his own with the long sword.  He had to do everything he could to keep them held back for this long but he was beginning to tire quickly.  Any longer without much help and he was most likely going to die.<br />
<br />
  When he reached the bottom of the hill Gnarm whispered a prayer to his god and each of the friends felt the healing and energizing power wash over them.  This last prayer must have taken quite a bit out of Gnarm because the dwarf staggered around and fell to a knee.<br />
<br />
“Gnarmie!”  Loryann shouted, actual concern for the dwarfs well being was very evident in her voice.<br />
<br />
“Don’t worry bout me lass I’m fine just a bit winded is all…kill dem dern giants!”<br />
<br />
Graydon felt Gnarm’s prayer lift the fatigue from his muscles and he upped his attack dodging and slicing at any open spot he could.  The shorter giant turned away from the paladin after noticing the dwarf in his weakened state.  He ran towards Gnarm with his hammer high, fully confident that the dwarf couldn’t get out of the way.  <br />
“GNARM!!!”  All three friends shouted as the giant’s weapon began it’s decent towards the dwarfs exposed head.  Gnarm turned in time to see his would be slayer bathed in a white light, it’s gigantic hammer stopping just inches from Gnarm’s head.  The face of the giant contorted in a stare of frustration and confusion.<br />
	<br />
“Whatever would you do with out me fatty!”  Fistel smirked.<br />
<br />
“Oh Brell!  Thought I was a goner again lad.”<br />
<br />
Loryann let a flurry of arrows loose towards the mesmerized giant, piercing it’s skull and sinking deep into it’s brain.  The giant collapsed having no idea where or how it had gone from victory to defeat so quickly.<br />
<br />
Gromdor saw that he was now outnumbered and doomed, he turned and ran away from the adventurers not wanting anything to do with them anymore.  “Oh no ye don’t ye dern frostie!”  Gnarm said as he spun in cicles getting his maul spinning around him.  Once he got the maul going fast enough he let it go and it hurdled through the night sky cracking the fleeing giant sharply in the back of the head.  The screech of quick and sudden pain could be heard from the giant as he collapsed face first into the snow.  Followed soon after by a dizzy dwarf.<br />
<br />
“Ihavedirenews.  Wemustgettothurgadinnow!”  Fistel’s mouth moved so quickly no one could understand him.<br />
<br />
“Whoa lad!  Slow down, we can’t understand ye.”<br />
<br />
Fistel took a deep breath and tried his best to explain to explain the need for haste at a slow pace.  The friends intently listened the Gnome’s tale of his visit to the Giant Fort.  The gnome struggled through the details, trying his hardest to speak slowly.  Once he was done the friends stood silent…the news was dire indeed.<br />
<br />
“By Brell Beard!  We have ta get ta Thurgadin and help dem prepare defenses let’s get moving!” Gnarm shouted as he gathered up his summoned weapon.  “No time for restin go go go!  We gots ta help me cousins!”<br />
<br />
The five travelers hurried through the Great Divide towards the great dwarven city of Thurgadin.  Gnarm chanting a prayer along the way to send a message on the wind to Kaladim and his fellow Champions of Brell.<br />
<br />
________________________________<br />
<br />
Dragdar Dragonblood, High Archon of Kaladim, sat at the end of a long oval table within the Temple of Brell, nestled deep within the caverns of Kaladim.  The signs of recently being awoken still in his eyes.  To his right sat Thorvyn Thunderfist, one of Kaladim’s finest warriors and devout Paladin of the Lord Underfoot.  The rest of the table was filled with dwarves, halflings and gnomes,  All Warleaders of the Champions of Brell.  Coming together hastily at this late hour at the behest of their leader and friend Dragdar.  It was not often that they all met and when a meeting was called this quickly it could not possibly be good.<br />
<br />
Dragdar leaned back in his chair and stroked his long white beard.  “Har har Well met again brothers and sisters!  It has been too long.”<br />
<br />
The room filled with a chorus of “Aye M’lord.”<br />
<br />
“I’m sorry ta say but the news t’day is not good.” Dragdar stood from his chair and began to pace around the table, patting his friends on the back and shaking their hands.  “Young brother Gnarm has sent me a dire message from the Great Divide.  It seems dat the giants in the area are massing for battle on our cousins in Thurgadin.”  Dragdar stopped and let everyone absorb this.  “He’s currently on his was to Thurgadin to help them prepare, and to let dem know whats comin.  But he fears dat Thurgadin could not possibly be able to amass much of a defense even with him an his friends help.”<br />
<br />
The mood in the room quickly changed as Dragdar laid down the events as he had heard them.  “Thurgadin and Gnarm be needin our help.  I bring this to you not to order ye inta battle but ta ask each of ye for yer help.”<br />
<br />
Drawing his flaming sword Thorvyn stood and addressed the Warleaders, “If’n yer comin speak up now wit a hearty ‘AYE’, if’n yer not…well I ain’t callin ya a longleg but yer bout as close ta one as I can find round here!”<br />
<br />
In response all the warleaders drew their weapons and in unison shouted, “AYE!”<br />
<br />
Dragdar smiled like a proud father watching his little dwarf throw his first hammer, “I knew me Champs wouldn’t let me down!  Gather up all da halfins an Dwarves an Gnomes ye can find brothers and sisters…we leave for Thurgadin immediately!”<br />
<br />
________________________________<br />
<br />
The group came to the great waterfall that hid the entrance to Thurgadin.  They had finally arrived, but that mug of ale and warm bed would have to wait.  Thurgadin needed to be awoken, the sun would soon be rising and with the sun came the giants.<br />
<br />
“Get me yer King!”  Gnarm yelled at one of the guards.<br />
<br />
“State yer name and yer business!”  The guard retorted, rather annoyed.<br />
<br />
“Bah!  I’m Gnarm Silverhand ye dolt and get yer dern King out here now or yer gonna be overrun by Giants!”<br />
<br />
The guards eyes lit up in surprise and he scrambled into Thurgadin.  Gnarm Silverhand was a great friend to Thurgadin and there were few who did not know his name here.  And if he said there were giants coming then by Brell…they’re were GIANTS coming!<br />
<br />
Gnarm tapped his foot on the ground he could see the sun starting to peek out from the horizon.  “Bah dern dwarves!  Hurry up!”  As he said this three individuals stepped out of the waterfall, all decked out in full dwarven ornate plate armor.<br />
<br />
“No time fer pleasantries me Lord.  The giants are coming and here be da plan.”  Gnarm layed out the plan he and his friends had devised on their run to Thurgadin as quickly as he could.  The King listened intently giving orders as Gnarm gave him the plan.  All the pieces were in place just as the first giant could be seen approaching Kaladim…but no one was prepared for what came behind that first giant.<br />
<br />
Covering the horizon marching shoulder to shoulder 500 giants strong descended on Thurgadin….<br />
<br />
To Be Continued…</font></p>
	
	<p></p>
